# meta-orhun-gui

This layer provides a custom, hardware-accelerated X11/XFCE graphical desktop environment for Yocto Project builds, specifically optimized for the Raspberry Pi 5. 

It features a completely minimal desktop setup, a pre-compiled Chromium browser with OpenGL support, and a seamless LXDM auto-login experience powered by systemd.

## Dependencies

This layer depends on several core and third-party OpenEmbedded layers:

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core
  layers: meta

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/meta-openembedded
  layers: meta-oe, meta-python, meta-networking, meta-xfce

  URI: git://git.yoctoproject.org/meta-raspberrypi
  branch: master

  URI: https://github.com/kraj/meta-clang
  branch: master

  URI: https://github.com/OSSystems/meta-browser
  layers: meta-chromium
  branch: master

## Core Features

* **Custom Distribution (`orhun-linux`):** Enforces `systemd` as the init manager, requires `usrmerge`, and globally enables `x11` and `opengl` features.
* **Minimal XFCE Desktop:** A stripped-down, highly responsive GUI environment.
* **Chromium Integration:** Fully hardware-accelerated web browser.
* **Display Manager:** Uses `lxdm` (bypassing the default `xserver-nodm-init`) to handle graphical sessions.
* **Auto-Login:** Systemd is configured to boot directly into `graphical.target`, and LXDM automatically logs into the default user without prompting.

## Default Credentials

The `orhun-gui` image provisions a default standard user for the auto-login session.

* **Username:** `user`
* **Password:** `1234`
* **Groups:** `video, audio, tty`

*Note: The password is set using a native SHA-512 hash in the image recipe to ensure compatibility with modern OpenEmbedded shadow utilities.*

